        <Parent_String>piers by form [300000955], piers (supporting elements) [300000953], piers and pier components [300052241], supporting and resisting elements [300078047], structural elements [300078048], structural elements and components for structural elements [300078046], architectural elements [300000885], components by specific context [300241584], components (objects parts) [300241583], Components (hierarchy name) [300241490], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Piers with an engaged figure of Osiris on the front, attached in such a manner that the pier, not the statue, supports the entablature; used in ancient Egyptian and Egyptian revival architecture. For statues that themselves directly support a superstructure, see descriptors collocated under the guide term "&lt;anthropomorphic supporting elements&gt;."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor pijlers met een aan de voorzijde bevestigde figuur van Osiris, die zodanig is bevestigd dat de pijler, niet het standbeeld, het entablement ondersteunt; gebruikt in de architectuur van het oude Egypte en de Egyptische herleving. Gebruik voor standbeelden die zelf rechtstreeks een bovenliggende constructie ondersteunen, de descriptoren onder "antropomorfe draagelementen".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
